// Complete Skill Handler
// Drives the workflow state machine forward after a skill finishes.
// Given the completed skill name, determines the next skill to invoke and updates session state.

The handler validates that the session's stored state matches the completed skill before using it
for routing. If they disagree, it falls back to deriving the state from the skill name.
Work item status updates happen BEFORE building the transition context so routing sees fresh statuses.

FUNCTION findNextPendingItem(workItems?) -> WorkItem | null
  Return the first work item with status === 'pending', or null if none.

---

FUNCTION findNextPendingBrainstormItem(workItems?) -> WorkItem | null
  Return the first work item with status === 'pending' (any type), or null.

---

FUNCTION findNextPendingRoughDraftItem(workItems?) -> WorkItem | null
  Return the first code or bugfix item with status === 'brainstormed', or null.

---

FUNCTION inferCurrentItem(stateId, workItems) -> WorkItem | null
  Map the current state to the expected item condition at that point in the workflow,
  and return the first matching item. Used as a defensive fallback when currentItem is null.
  States handled: rough-draft-blueprint, brainstorm-validating, task-planning, systematic-debugging.

---

FUNCTION completeSkill(project, session, completedSkill) -> CompleteSkillOutput  EXPORT
  CALLS: getSessionState (collab-state), migrateWorkItems (state-machine), getSkillForState (state-machine), skillToState (state-machine), getStatusUpdateForSkill (transitions), inferCurrentItem (complete-skill), buildTransitionContext (transitions), getNextState (transitions), syncTasksFromTaskGraph (task-sync), getSessionState (collab-state), resolveToSkillState (transitions), updateSessionState (collab-state), updateTaskDiagram (task-diagram)
  Step 1: Read session state. Defensively parse workItems if stored as a string.
  Step 1b: Migrate legacy work item statuses ('documented' → 'brainstormed', old intermediate → 'complete').
  Step 2: Determine current state ID. IF session state has a state field and its skill matches
    completedSkill, use it directly. ELSE fall back to skillToState lookup. Throw if unknown.
  Step 2a: IF the completed state triggers a status update and workItems exist:
    IF currentItem is set, update that item's status.
    ELSE infer the item via inferCurrentItem, log a warning, and update the inferred item.
  Step 2b: IF completing execute-batch, increment currentBatch counter.
  Step 3: Build transition context from session state and current item type.
  Step 4: Get the next raw state ID. IF none, return { next_skill: null, action: 'none' }.
  Step 4a: Pre-resolve item-type-router so downstream routers get proper item selection.
  Step 4a: IF entering brainstorm-item-router or work-item-router, find next pending brainstorm item.
    IF found, set it as currentItem and rebuild context with its type.
    IF none, clear currentItem and rebuild context.
  Step 4a: IF entering rough-draft-item-router, find next pending rough-draft item.
    IF found, set it as currentItem and rebuild context.
    IF none, clear currentItem and rebuild context.
  Step 5a: IF entering batch-router, mark all remaining brainstormed code/bugfix items complete,
    then sync tasks from the task graph. Rebuild context from fresh state after sync.
  Step 5b: Resolve the next state through any routing nodes to find the next skill-bearing state.
    IF none resolved, return { next_skill: null, action: 'none' }.
  Step 7: Save updated session state: new state ID, item updates, batch counter, migrated workItems.
  Step 9: IF in implementation phase and batches exist, update the task diagram (non-fatal on failure).
  Return { next_skill, params: buildParams(resolved state, session state) }.

---

FUNCTION buildParams(stateId, sessionState) -> params | undefined
  Build the params object for the next skill invocation.
  Include item_number if currentItem is set.
  Include batch_index if currentBatch is set.
  Return undefined if no params are needed.

---

FUNCTION stateToSkill(stateId) -> string | null                                  EXPORT
  CALLS: getSkillForState (state-machine)
  Return the skill name for the given state ID (reverse of skillToState).
